abstract: Climate change and other conditions don’t respect boundary lines.
snippet: Climate change and other conditions don’t respect boundary lines.
lead_paragraph: TEL AVIV — To get a different perspective on the Trump-Kushner peace plan, I decided to call the best Middle East analyst I know. Her name is Mother Nature.
headline_main: Mother Nature Scoffs at Trump’s Mideast Peace Plan
headline_print_headline: Mother Nature Rejects Trump Peace Plan

abstract: The president emphasized a “blue collar” boom in his speech to Congress. But workers in those industries have seen a slowdown — or even losses — in jobs.
snippet: The president emphasized a “blue collar” boom in his speech to Congress. But workers in those industries have seen a slowdown — or even losses — in jobs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump used his State of the Union address on Tuesday to tick off a laundry list of economic gains, citing record low unemployment for women, higher incomes for households and a “blue collar” boom that he said is underway across America.

headline_main: Coronavirus, State of the Union, Iowa: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: One night each year, the Capitol is transformed for the State of the Union. This year, it happens to be the day before President Trump’s likely acquittal.
snippet: One night each year, the Capitol is transformed for the State of the Union. This year, it happens to be the day before President Trump’s likely acquittal.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the uncertain turmoil of American politics, there is reassurance in the predictable pomp of the State of the Union.

abstract: The “Fox News Sunday” anchor told The Times that the accusation from Steve Bannon was “utter foolishness.”
snippet: The “Fox News Sunday” anchor told The Times that the accusation from Steve Bannon was “utter foolishness.”
lead_paragraph: On Dec. 10, 2016, the Fox News anchor Chris Wallace spent several hours interviewing Donald J. Trump for an episode of “Fox News Sunday.” Mr. Wallace spoke with Mr. Trump at Trump Tower in Manhattan and then flew with Mr. Trump and his advisers to the Army-Navy football game in Baltimore, where their conversation continued.

abstract: Seventh Generation, known for a toilet tissue made of recycled paper, will follow the State of the Union address with a 60-second commercial on three networks.
snippet: Seventh Generation, known for a toilet tissue made of recycled paper, will follow the State of the Union address with a 60-second commercial on three networks.
lead_paragraph: On the chance that President Trump does not mention climate change during his State of the Union address Tuesday night, Seventh Generation, a company known for eco-friendly products, has taken steps to make sure the issue is a prime-time talking point.

headline_main: Even if Trump Doesn’t Bring Up Climate Change Tonight, This Ad Will

abstract: The first-term congresswoman from Texas had a visceral response to President Trump’s State of the Union address last year. Now she has the chance to rebut him directly.
snippet: The first-term congresswoman from Texas had a visceral response to President Trump’s State of the Union address last year. Now she has the chance to rebut him directly.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Trump delivered his State of the Union address in 2019, he pointed to El Paso as a sign of the success of his immigration policies, claiming it had been transformed from “one of our nation’s most dangerous cities” to “one of the safest cities in our country” by the construction of a border wall.

headline_main: Veronica Escobar to Focus on Health Care, Guns in Spanish-Language Response to Trump

abstract: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
snippet: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Democratic officials in Iowa on Tuesday provided a measure of clarity to the muddled outcome of its statewide caucuses, releasing a delayed first wave of partial results that showed Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders with a preliminary lead and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. falling well behind the other top-tier candidates.

abstract: A Brooklyn organization trains canvassers to engage with prospective voters about their hopes and disappointments, not just give them a candidate’s talking points.
snippet: A Brooklyn organization trains canvassers to engage with prospective voters about their hopes and disappointments, not just give them a candidate’s talking points.
lead_paragraph: It’s a truism that America has been gripped by tribalism, polarization and rage. But what if it were possible to have a civil conversation with an unlike-minded stranger? To find common ground and even persuade that person to think differently?
